snippet: The delays are the result of longshoremen and shippers negotiating a new contract after a previous labor deal ended in July.
abstract: Delays at West Coast seaports have held up shipments as longshoremen and shippers negotiate new contract; among delays is record apple crop from Washington State, planned for shipment to over 60 countries for holiday season.
lead_paragraph: The delays are the result of longshoremen and shippers negotiating a new contract after a previous labor deal ended in July.

headline.main: Washington Apples Delayed at West Coast Seaports
headline.print_headline: Washington Apples Delayed at West Coast Seaports
